import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import { useAuth } from '../context/AuthContext'; import { FaUser, FaSignOutAlt, FaHome, FaBell, FaFileAlt, FaSubscript, FaCreditCard } from 'react-icons/fa'; import axios from 'axios'; const UserDashboard = () => { const { user, logout } = useAuth(); const [userSubscriptions, setUserSubscriptions] = useState([]); const [userTransactions, setUserTransactions] = useState([]); const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true); useEffect(() => { if (user?.email) { fetchUserData(); } }, [user]); const fetchUserData = async () => { try { const [subsRes, transRes] = await Promise.all([ axios.get('http://localhost:8000/api/subscriptions/'), axios.get('http://localhost:8000/api/transactions/') ]); // Filter data for current user const userSubs = subsRes.data.filter(sub => sub.user_email === user.email); const userTrans = transRes.data.filter(trans => trans.user_name && trans.user_name.includes(user.name)); setUserSubscriptions(userSubs); setUserTransactions(userTrans); } catch (error) { console.error('Error fetching user data:', error); } finally { setLoading(false); } }; const handleLogout = () => { logout(); window.location.href = '/login'; }; return (
